2)Disk usage - 
df: Shows disk space usage of all mounted filesystems
df -h: Shows disk usage in human-readable format (GB/MB)
du: Displays disk usage of files and directories
du . : Shows disk usage of the current directory

3) Process Management - ps, top, fuser, kill, nohup, 

Interview: Commands like df and du monitor disk usage, top and ps track processes, free and vmstat show memory and system stats, 
and kill, fuser, and nohup are used for process management.

fuser: Identifies which process is using a file or port

kill: Terminates a process using its PID

free: Displays system memory (RAM) usage
free -h - gives details on free memory

nohup - Runs a process in the background that continues after logout
$nohup free -h appends the output of free -h to a file nohup.out
Now the command $ nohup df -h 
Will append the output of df -h after the previously added content in nohup.out
Check with the command $ cat nohup.out
To display first 5 lines of nohup.out file, the command is
$ head -n 5 nohup.out
The last 5 lines will be displayed by the command
$ tail -n 5 nohup.out

